# Team Members (shared)

Copy this file to `.github/team-members.md` and edit. Configs that set `team_members_file` will resolve to this list, so the team can co-own membership without per-product config diffs.

The agent uses this list to **exclude team members from creator-influence tracking** (no point measuring your own teammates as community advocates) and to **attribute interventions by owner** in `scout-creators` view.

## Members

| Display name | Handles | Platforms | Role | GitHub |
|--------------|---------|-----------|------|--------|
| Jane Doe | @janedoe | bluesky, x, linkedin | Developer Advocate | janedoe |
| Pat Lee | @patlee | github, devto | Engineer | patlee |

## Resolution rules

When a config has `team_members_file: .github/team-members.md`:

1. Load this file's `## Members` table.
2. Optionally extend with the config's own `## Team Members` section (these are merged in addition, not replacing).
3. Match against creators by `(platform, handle)` tuple — exact match required.
4. Owner names referenced in `scout-creators log-intervention` MUST match a `Display name` in this list.
